'''Andrés Alberto Andrade Cedeño''' (born 16 October 1998) is a Panamanian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for Austrian club [[LASK]] and the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=lask.at [[LASK]]|url=https://www.lask.at/en/m/player/andres-andrade|title=Andres Andrade|language=de}}</ref>

==Club career==
On 31 August 2021, the last day of the 2021 summer transfer window, Andrade joined [[Bundesliga]] club [[Arminia Bielefeld]] on loan for the [[2021–22 Arminia Bielefeld season|2021–22 season]] from [[Austrian Football Bundesliga|Austrian Bundesliga]] side [[LASK]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ahlers |first1=Jan |title=Arminia schlägt am "Deadline Day" zu: Andrade kommt aus Linz |url=https://www.nw.de/sport/dsc_arminia_bielefeld/23080634_Arminia-schlaegt-am-Deadline-Day-zu-Andrade-kommt-aus-Linz.html |access-date=31 August 2021 |work=Neue Westfälische |date=31 August 2021 |language=de |archive-date=31 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210831075252/https://www.nw.de/sport/dsc_arminia_bielefeld/23080634_Arminia-schlaegt-am-Deadline-Day-zu-Andrade-kommt-aus-Linz.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Arminia Bielefeld secured an option to sign him permanently which they did in June 2022.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|url=https://www.kicker.de/luecke-geschlossen-bielefeld-holt-andrade-aus-linz-870077/artikel/|title=Lücke geschlossen: Bielefeld holt Andrade aus Linz|access-date=28 April 2024|archive-date=29 May 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230529140534/https://www.kicker.de/luecke-geschlossen-bielefeld-holt-andrade-aus-linz-870077/artikel|url-status=live}}</ref>
<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Telemetro|url=https://www.telemetro.com/deportes/andres-andrade-sale-goleado-y-eliminado-la-dfb-pokal-n5788760/|title=Andrés Andrade sale goleado y eliminado de la DFB-Pokal|access-date=28 April 2024|archive-date=26 December 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221226234743/https://www.telemetro.com/deportes/andres-andrade-sale-goleado-y-eliminado-la-dfb-pokal-n5788760|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=prensa.com|url=https://www.prensa.com/deportes/el-bayern-logra-trabajada-victoria-ante-el-arminia-bielefeld-el-panameno-andres-andrade-fue-titular//|title=El Bayern logra trabajada victoria ante el Arminia Bielefeld; el panameño Andrés Andrade fue titular|access-date=28 April 2024|archive-date=26 December 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221226234740/https://www.prensa.com/deportes/el-bayern-logra-trabajada-victoria-ante-el-arminia-bielefeld-el-panameno-andres-andrade-fue-titular/|url-status=live}}</ref>

In June 2023, Andrade returned to LASK on a four-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lask.at/rueckkehr-zum-lask-innenverteidiger-andres-andrade-ist-wieder-schwarz-weisser/|title=RÜCKKEHR ZUM LASK: INNENVERTEIDIGER ANDRÉS ANDRADE IST WIEDER SCHWARZ-WEISSER|trans-title=RETURN TO LASK: CENTRAL DEFENDER ANDRÉS ANDRADE IS BLACK AND WHITE AGAIN|language=German|website=www.lask.at|date=12 June 2023}}</ref>

==International career==
Andrade represented the [[Panama national under-20 football team|Panama U20 national team]] at the [[2017 CONCACAF U-20 Championship]], scoring once.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Soccerway|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/02/21/nc-america/concacaf-u20/panama-youth/st-kitts-and-nevis-under-20/2377202/|date=21 February 2017|title=Panama U20 v Saint Kitts and Nevis U20 game report|access-date=22 November 2018|archive-date=15 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180615054019/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/02/21/nc-america/concacaf-u20/panama-youth/st-kitts-and-nevis-under-20/2377202/|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 16 November 2018, Andrade made his debut for the senior [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]] against [[Honduras national football team|Honduras]] as a 72nd-minute substitute for [[Erick Davis]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ESPN]]|url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/lineups?gameId=528271|title=Honduras v Panama game report|date=16 November 2018|access-date=22 November 2018|archive-date=22 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181122092445/http://www.espn.com/soccer/lineups?gameId=528271|url-status=live}}</ref>

